Transect notes: Rock shelf releif with turf <0.5cm, fronting aimakapaʻa fishpond. Rubble shelf less than 1m deep with sand beach inshore about 3m.

North end of beach fronting Aimakapaʻa fish pond. Sandy with unusual cyanobacterial bloom like growth along the sand. We saw this soft brown cyanobacteria also at the seep at Kahaluʻu. <1m deep, 2m offshore of sandy beach.

Offshore of rocky intertidal shelf, ~15m offshore, ~1m depth, surge and wave action. Urchin Echinometra mathaei shaped reef grooves with turf algae on top, coralline algae inside urchin grooves. About 20 e. mathaei per quadrat

Quadrat Notes: Mussels: Brachidontes crebristriatus, nahawele, li'i li'i
Transect notes: Rocky intertidal with Ulva enteromorpha growth and red turf. Some Pahoehoe lava flats with large (50-80cm), irregular boulders. Rocks look mostly clean with little algal growth. 2-3m from sandy beach inland. Wide shallow shelf ~10 m wide between beach and water level, but would be wet with high tide.

Kolea bird, small other seabird (sanderling, hunakai bird) family of 3, herron hunting in rocks, pupu limpets ~300 from .75cm-10mm. Pupu=Nerita picea. Same rocky intertidal shelf as the previous transect, but further north. Shelf extends ~10 m offshore, with tidepools near the water line. This transect is at the shoreward side, about 3m from the sandy beach. Dry with little water in the cracks. Strange coating of "microbial film" mixed with U. enteromorpha. We noticed the inland, springward Ulva tends to be enteromorpha at this site, giving way to U. lactuca growth forms where the tide line was at low tide. Perhaps U. lactuca forms cannot persist the prolonged exposure to air that these U. enteromorpha are experiencing.

Juvenile herbivorous fish ~300<10cm, 2 heron feeding, pink wana & black wana ~20. Transect in the channel near the fish trap, seaward edge of large rocky intertidal shelf. Consistent wave action. Visible seeps. YSI mesurement taken. Almost 100% turf cover <10mm

Quadrat Notes: Intertidal shelf, near north edge. ~3m from sandy beach, ~1m from water line. Exposed with turf and crusts. 2 cowries <3cm, 1 spotted shell <2cm, black urchins  (Echinometra oblonga) 4-8cm

Transect notes: Juvenile and adult herron, pupu Nerita picea shells ~50/m, juvenile Acanthurus trigostegus, white eye fish juvenile, slippery limu everywhere Zebrazoma flavescens (oʻopu). Pool of water shoreward of rocky intertidal shelf. ~5m from water line, ~3m from sandy beach
Inside fish trap, seaward of smaller rock wall enclosure. Rocky bottom with light cover turf almost 100% cover, <.3 m deep

Our very first transect!! Calm, shallow <0.3m depth sandy to rubbly inshore region, inland of fish trap. Lots of tiny pupu Nerita picea  snails. Rubble with green (cladophora?) and red turf patches. Orange crust. Ends on shallow rock shelf covered in green turf.
